race.comment: MUM KNOWS (12) led from the outset and showed plenty of fight under pressure to hang on and record her maiden win when resuming over this course and distance 23 days ago. That was her first run under John Shelton so the change looks to have done the trick. Worth following now. OFCOURSEIAM (9) last raced when down the track at Wyong in August. Best form last prep was at six furlongs so this may be a touch short, but while fresh she remains in the picture. RAISED BY WOLVES (13) started favourite but after an awkward jump could only manage third when resuming here at this distance recently. Saves most of his good runs for this circuit so must be kept very safe. Last start Taree maiden winner EX WIFE (2) is progressing nicely and is not out of place in this company.
